<dl id="n36063e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36063e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36063e"> 63(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mortella Tower / Myrtilla Tower</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Another idea is that they were so called from the name of a Corsican who invented this style of defence, but the correct one seems to be that they owe their name to <mark>Mortella (<i>Myrtle</i>) Bay in Corsica</mark>, where the English forces found themselves resisted with great force by one such tower in 1794 &hellip; <small> A. Peter, <a name="APDF2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APDF2"><cite title="source">Dublin Fragments, social and historic</cite></a> (1925) 138 [Regarding the Irish Martello Towers]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
